The paper proposes a novel approach for discriminative classification using evolutionary algorithms. The focus is on optimizing the total loss value for classification, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper also compares the proposed algorithm with well-established and state-of-the-art classification algorithms, which suggests that it belongs to the machine learning subfield. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
